docs.snippet: The Cunard screw steamer Karnak, Capt. BROWN, arrived at an early hour yesterday morning from Havana, vid Nassau. Left Havana on the 2d inst., and Nassau on the 4th, and anchored on her arrival at the lower Quarantine.

headline.main: What Knowledge is of Most Worth.

docs.lead_paragraph: The Westminster Review, for July, contains "a very able and common sense article, written in the cold-blooded and unimpassioned style peculiar to that philosophical Quarterly, entitled "What Knowledge is of Most Worth." It is purely materialistic, of course, and, as far as it goes, is eminently practical; whether every one will agree in the conclusions at which it arrives, is doubtful;

docs.lead_paragraph: A MAN ACCIDENTALLY SHOT AND KILLED BY A POLICEMAN.--A sad occurrence transpired on Saturday evening, about 7 o'clock, in Spruce-street, near Gold. Officer DOBKEE, of the Second Ward, was asked to shoot a house which had become unmanageable during the day in Chatham-street, and running away had brought up against a post in the locality above-named, where it received such injuries that it could not live.
